document_data.Powers:
The sword's edge was hard to dull.{{cite book/Lady of Poison|159|16}} Against some demons, the blade strobed green, causing their hide to erupt in green flame by simply brushing them.{{cite book/Lady of Poison|193|19}} Against greater demons, their skin peeled itself back on contact.{{cite book/Lady of Poison|198|20}}
The blade had defensive powers as well, being able to prevent attacks with a flash of light, but such things caused it to expend its charge.{{cite book/Lady of Poison|207|21}} but it could regain its charge by being exposed to sunlight.{{cite book/Lady of Poison|252-253|27}}
The blade also had the power to launch rays of powerful radiance like that of the sun, down to the ability to annihilate vampires.{{cite book/Lady of Poison|285-286|30}}

For a wielder with some knowledge of history, fluency in the elven language, and fair skill at arms, Dymondheart could also progress differently, showing other powers.{{cite book/Weapons of Legacy|79}}
